      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Putting It Together: Claude + PgBouncer Pattern"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import asyncio\nimport anthropic\nimport asyncpg\n\nclaude = anthropic.AsyncAnthropic()\n\nasync def handle_request(\n    pool: asyncpg.Pool,\n    user_id: int,\n    user_message: str,\n) -> str:\n    # Step 1: read context (holds DB conn for ~5ms)\n    async with pool.acquire() as conn:\n        row = await conn.fetchrow(\n            \"SELECT system_prompt, context FROM users WHERE id = $1\", user_id\n        )\n    # Connection returned to pool HERE — during Claude call, no conn held\n\n    # Step 2: call Claude (1–15s, zero DB connections consumed)\n    response = await claude.messages.create(\n        model=\"claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        max_tokens=1024,\n        system=row[\"system_prompt\"],\n        messages=[\n            {\"role\": \"user\", \"content\": user_message},\n        ],\n    )\n    answer = response.content[0].text\n\n    # Step 3: write result (holds DB conn for ~5ms)\n    async with pool.acquire() as conn:\n        await conn.execute(\n            \"\"\"\n            INSERT INTO chat_messages (user_id, role, content)\n            VALUES ($1, 'assistant', $2)\n            \"\"\",\n            user_id, answer,\n        )\n    # Connection returned to pool again\n\n    return answer\n\nasync def main():\n    pool = await asyncpg.create_pool(\n        dsn=\"postgresql://user:pass@pgbouncer:5432/mydb\",\n        min_size=2,\n        max_size=20,\n        statement_cache_size=0,  # required for transaction mode\n    )\n    # Process 100 concurrent requests — only ~20 DB conns needed\n    tasks = [\n        handle_request(pool, user_id=i, user_message=\"Hello\")\n        for i in range(100)\n    ]\n    results = await asyncio.gather(*tasks)\n    print(f\"{len(results)} responses\")\n\nasyncio.run(main())"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "With this pattern, 100 concurrent Claude requests require at most 40 database connections (20 for reads, 20 for writes at the same instant) rather than 100. In practice, because the Claude call dominates latency, most connections are idle most of the time and far fewer than 40 are active simultaneously."
          }
        ]
